Participants are randomly divided into five groups (1-5), each designated as a bidder with fixed roles throughout the 30-round game.
At the start of each round, bidders receive a private signal (a shared value estimate with noise), while the common value (CV) is disclosed after the auction concludes.
The price starts at 0 and increases automatically (by 1 point every 650 milliseconds). Bidders can click the "Exit" button at any time to leave, and they cannot rejoin after exiting.
Information hiding: Bidders cannot see other bidders' exit prices.
When four bidders withdraw, the remaining bidder becomes the winner and pays the price of the fourth withdrawing bidder.
Profit calculation: Winner's profit = CV - the fourth-place withdrawal price, with all other bidders' profits being 0.
Your goal is to become the winner with the highest profit value.
